WHAT IS TRIOPS?
---------------
Triops is an SA:MP-specific toolchain designed for debugging, compiling, and package management.
It is primarily built using Bash (90%) with some Python3 integration.

KEEPING UP-TO-DATE
------------------
Always update using:
    sync
or for a full update:
    syncc

PREREQUISITES
-------------
Before starting, ensure you have the following:

1. INSTALL `triops/workspace` SCRIPT
  - (Stable)
   Download via GNU/Wget:
       wget -q --show-progress -O workspace https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vilksons/triops/refs/heads/main/Scripts/workspace

   With auto-execution:
       wget -q --show-progress -O workspace https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vilksons/triops/refs/heads/main/Scripts/workspace && \
       chmod +x workspace && bash ./workspace

  - (Testing)
   Download via GNU/Wget:
       wget -q --show-progress -O workspace https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vilksons/triops/refs/heads/testing/Scripts/workspace

   With auto-execution:
       wget -q --show-progress -O workspace https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vilksons/triops/refs/heads/testing/Scripts/workspace && \
       chmod +x workspace && bash ./workspace

2. INSTALL REQUIRED PACKAGES
   Full list available at:
   https://github.com/vilksons/triops/wiki/Required-Packages

INSTALLATION
------------
Supported Platforms:
- Linux, Darwin, Windows, macOS, and Android via:
  - WSL: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install
  - Git Bash: https://git-scm.com/downloads
  - MSYS2: https://www.msys2.org/
  - mingw-w64: https://www.mingw-w64.org/
  - Cygwin: https://www.cygwin.com/
  - Babun: https://github.com/babun/babun
  - Termux: https://termux.dev/en/
  - UserLAnd: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=tech.ula&hl=id&pli=1
  - Linux Deploy: https://github.com/meefik/linuxdeploy

INSTALLATION STEPS
------------------
1. Open the terminal.
2. Make the `workspace` script executable:
       chmod +x workspace
3. Run the script:
       bash ./workspace

USAGE
-----
FILE RENAMING
-------------
Rename `yourmode.pwn` files to a project-appropriate format (e.g., `yourmode.io.pwn`) for consistency.

COMPILATION
-----------
- Default compilation:
       compile .
- Specific file compilation:
       compile yourmode.pwn
- Compilation with options:
       compile yourmode.pwn opt1 opt2 opt3

STARTING & DEBUGGING
--------------------
- Run a compiled script:
       running yourmode.pwn
- Debug a script:
       debug yourmode.pwn

CONFIGURATION `lang.json`
---------------------------
    {
        "amx_flags": [
            "-;+",
            "-(+",
            "-d3"
        ],
        "include_paths": "pawno/include",
        "exclude_paths": [
            "includes",
            "includes2",
            "includes3"
        ],
        "samp_log": "server_log.txt",
        "server_conf": "server.cfg",
        "main_server": "main.pwn",
        "samp_executable": "samp03svr",
        "include_dir": "pawno/include",
        "plugins_dir": "plugins",
        "bot_token": "gsk_abcd",
        "bot_model": "qwen-2.5-32b",
        "bot_profile": "",
        "remcache_auto": "true",
        "repository": "stable"
    }

CONFIGURATION DETAILS
------------------------------
  o amx_flags
    option Flags: https://github.com/vilksons/triops/wiki/Compiler-Option
  o include_paths
    Default compiler include directory.
  o exclude_paths
    Directories excluded from compilation.                      
  o samp_log
    SA-MP server log file.                                      
  o server_conf
    SA-MP server configuration file.     (TligPac)
  o main_server
    SA-MP main server file. (TligPac)           
  o samp_executable
    SA-MP server executable.                                    
  o include_dir
    Package manager include directory (TligPac).                
  o plugins_dir
    Directory for `.dll` and `.so` plugins (TligPac).           
  o bot_token
    API key from https://console.groq.com/keys
  o bot_model
    AI model from https://console.groq.com/                     
  o bot_profile
    Additional chatbot configuration.                           
  o remcache_auto
    Auto-remove `/.cache` (true/false).                         
  o repository
    Repository of Triops for Sync - (stable/testing) ~ testing faster before main

EXAMPLE: `include_paths` USAGE
------------------------------
    If a script inside `includes/` is not recognized, define:
        "include_paths": "includes"
    in `lang.json`.

EXAMPLE DIRECTORY STRUCTURE
---------------------------
    samp-server/
    ├── gamemodes/
    │   ├── mygamemode.pwn
    │   └── ...
    │
    ├── includes/
    │   ├── customFile.pwn
    │   ├── anotherFile.pwn
    │   └── ...
    │
    └── server.cfg

PACKAGE MANAGER - TLIGPAC
-------------------------
    Triops operates in two modes:
    1. Ops Mode (default, without package manager)
    2. TligPac Mode (enables package fetching and installation)

SWITCHING TO TLIGPAC MODE
-------------------------
    tligpac

EXITING TLIGPAC MODE
--------------------
    exit

PACKAGE MANAGEMENT
------------------
Installing Packages:
    install github/samp-incognito/samp-streamer-plugin

Removing Packages:
    remove streamer

Use `autoinstall` to download packages from the tligpac cache from previous `install` results.
    autoinstall
  
TLIGPAC CONFIGURATION
---------------------
TligPac uses `tligpac.toml` or `tligpac.json`.

Example `tligpac.toml`:
    [package]
    urls = [
      "github/user/repository",
      "gitlab/user/repository",
      "sourceforge/user/repository"
    ]

Example `tligpac.json`:
    {
        "package": [
            "github/user/repository",
            "gitlab/user/repository",
            "sourceforge/user/repository"
        ]
    }

